## 9. Knowledge System (optional)

Some builders persist learning across sessions. If you want this, describe how.

**Examples**

- "Write a session journal at the end of each Claude Code session. One file per day. Path: ~/.claude/projects/{project}/memory/session_YYYY-MM-DD.md."
- "Maintain a past-mistakes.md per project. Every bug fix gets a class-of-error entry."
- "Decision records live in docs/decisions/. One file per significant choice."

If you do not want this, delete the section.

```
[Your knowledge system or delete this section]
```

---

## How to verify the file works

After you fill in the spine, open Claude Code and type:

```
summarize my CLAUDE.md
```

Claude should return a summary that matches what you wrote. If it does not, the file is not loading. Check that it is at `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md` exactly.

---

## A note on length

A good first CLAUDE.md is between 60 and 200 lines. The spine above might fill to about 150 lines when complete. If you find yourself adding more rules every week, you are doing it right. If the file passes 400 lines, split off project-specific stuff into project CLAUDE.md files and keep this one global.

